  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist? Each chain has been specifically added to the source code. Geth gets around this limitation by allowing users to specify their own networkid and bootnode.\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\nI want to use a chain unknown to private or new chains not yet hardcoded into erigon.\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nThe cleanest way to provide this type of functionality is to allow ingestion of a config file say ~/erigon.yml or `${XDG_DATA_HOME:-~/.local/share}/erigon/config.yml`.\r\n\r\nProposed format:\r\n```\r\nchains:\r\n  private_network_name:\r\n    networkid: 2001\r\n    bootnodes: \r\n    - enode://{key}@69.420.69.420:30303\r\n    \r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\nYes, I can work on this feature.",
